    "comment": "Rationale: A fusion construct of the beta4 subunit with GFP at its N terminus was overexpressed in low density hippocampal cultures (viral infection). This displayed a punctate pattern in axons and showed partial colocalization with the synaptic vesicle marker synaptobrevin II (antibody staining).\n\n30/6/2017 Pim\n- In these experiments only the presynaptic neuron is labeled (low density cultures, not all cells infected with the virus). This way co-localization observed with this \"sub-resolution\" technique can be explained as \"presynaptic\" localization.. Experimental description: Continental hippocampal cultures were prepared from rat brains. After 9-14 days in culture cells were infected with activated Semliki Forest virus containing the appropriate cDNAs.\n\n30/6/2017 Pim\nOver-expressed protein is of rat species: \"The rat β4 cDNA (13) was amplified with the following primer pairs, ....\"",
